<TITLE> Seaports again asked to show cautionary signal 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, September 06 (bdnews24.com) - Deep convection and steep pressure gradient persist over North Bay, the met office said Thursday. Squally weather may continue to affect the maritime ports. The met office asked the maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla to hoist local cautionary signal 3. Low-Lying areas of the coastal districts and their off-shore Islands and chars are likely to be inundated by a wind driven surge of height 1-3 feet above normal astronomical tide. All fishing boats and trawlers over North Bay and deep sea were asked to remain close to the coast and proceed with caution until further notice. bdn
